entries.title: Investor Lawsuit Against Elon Musk and Tesla Goes to a Jury
entries.description: The case centers on whether investors lost money because they believed Mr. Musk’s social media posts about taking Tesla private in 2018.

entries.title: ‘My Watch Thinks I’m Dead’
entries.description: 911 dispatchers are buried under an avalanche of false, automated distress calls from skiers and other Apple device owners who are very much alive.

entries.title: How ChatGPT Kicked Off an A.I. Arms Race
entries.description: Even inside the company, the chatbot’s popularity has come as something of a shock.

entries.title: TikTok’s “Transparency and Accountability Center” + ChatGPT’s Origin Story + Kevin Systrom’s Artifact App
entries.description: Casey becomes a content moderator, Kevin breaks some news on OpenAI and Instagram’s co-founder reveals his new project.

entries.title: Tech’s Biggest Companies Discover Austerity, to the Relief of Investors
entries.description: After years of expansion and billions in profits, Big Tech is pulling back from its famously lavish spending as a long boom finally ends.
